summary: This is a certification from Municipal Credit Union responding to a subpoena duces tecum, confirming the accuracy and completeness of produced financial records for a specified reference number. It indicates checks and credit card statements were not applicable to the request and notes that SARs/CTRs would be handled separately.

persons.name: Danielle Jones
persons.context: Authorized custodian of records for Municipal Credit Union who certifies the accuracy and completeness of documents produced in response to a subpoena.

persons.name: Patricia Gonzalez
persons.context: Notary Public who notarized the certification document, qualified in Queens County, New York.

events.title: Subpoena Response Certification
events.description: Municipal Credit Union, through Danielle Jones, certifies the production of records in response to a subpoena duces tecum under reference SUB9316-DJ.

locations: Municipal Credit Union, PO Box 3205 CBS, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: Municipal Credit Union produced records in response to a subpoena duces tecum under reference SUB9316-DJ.
The certification states that checks and credit card statements were 'Not Applicable' to the subpoena request.
The document notes that Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) or Currency Transaction Reports (CTRs) are not included and would be handled separately by the BSA Department.
